This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for semi-supervised learning tasks. It also involves the use of self-training, which is a common technique in semi-supervised learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GANs are often used for image generation tasks. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) as it deals with the generation of images.
